                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/biol-112" class="program-course-title">
              BIOL 112 Cell and Molecular Biology (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-18748" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Biology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Biology (Sci)              : The cell: ultrastructure, division, chemical constituents and reactions. Bioenergetics: photosynthesis and respiration. Principles of genetics, the molecular basis of inheritance and biotechnology.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Joseph Alan Dent, Frieder Schöck (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Winter</li>
              <li>2 hours lecture and 3.5 hours laboratory/seminar</li>
              <li>Restriction: Not open to students who have taken or are taking CEGEP objective 00XU or equivalent; or BIOL 115; or AEBI 122</li>
              <li>Attendance at first lab is mandatory to confirm registration in the course.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

