                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/phar-300" class="program-course-title">
              PHAR 300 Drug Action (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-32984" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Pharmacology and Therapeutics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Pharmacology and Therapeutics              : Principles of pharmacology and toxicology. Frequently encountered drugs will be used as a focus to illustrate sites and mechanisms of action, distribution, metabolism, elimination and adverse side effects.          </p>

